@startuml
title Public Catalogue: Customer Browse/Search -> View Book Detail (Happy Path)

actor Customer as U
participant "Web Browser" as B
participant "Catalogue Web App" as W
participant "REST API (v1)" as API
database "Inventory DB" as DB

U -> B: Open catalogue page
B -> W: GET /catalogue
W -> API: GET /api/v1/genres\nGET /api/v1/authors (for filters)
API -> DB: SELECT genres, authors (active)
DB --> API: Genres + Authors
API --> W: Filter metadata
W --> B: Render catalogue + filters

U -> B: Enter keyword + select genre/author filters\n+ sort/pagination
B -> W: GET /catalogue?q=...&genres=...&authors=...&sort=...&page=1
W -> API: GET /api/v1/books?q=...&genres=...&authors=...&sort=...&page=1
API -> DB: Query books by title/author + filters\nORDER BY + LIMIT/OFFSET
DB --> API: Books page + total count
API --> W: 200 OK\n{items[], page, pageSize, total}
W --> B: Render results list + pagination

U -> B: Click a book result
B -> W: GET /books/{bookId}
W -> API: GET /api/v1/books/{bookId}
API -> DB: SELECT book + authors + genres + availability
DB --> API: Book detail record
API --> W: 200 OK\n{book, authors, genres, availability}
W --> B: Render book detail page

@enduml